1
00:00:04,366 --> 00:00:06,040
Women, they really take their time!

2
00:00:06,065 --> 00:00:07,775
Right?! They're taking forever!

3
00:00:10,922 --> 00:00:13,822
Dad, it’s the bakery’s reopening today.

4
00:00:14,180 --> 00:00:15,180
Exactly!

5
00:00:15,205 --> 00:00:16,805
But it looks like we’re
going to miss the opening!

6
00:00:16,830 --> 00:00:17,936
That’s what I’m saying, exactly!

7
00:00:17,961 --> 00:00:19,825
I know! Women!

8
00:00:20,186 --> 00:00:22,600
My love, Lola Maxi, Tash!

9
00:00:23,413 --> 00:00:24,413
Oh!

10
00:00:47,376 --> 00:00:49,827
Applause! Wow!

11
00:00:52,898 --> 00:00:54,838
I want the whole world –

12
00:00:55,525 --> 00:01:01,754
the universe, rather – to know that
am confidently beautiful with a heart.

13
00:01:02,551 --> 00:01:05,104
Ah! Applause! Wow!

14
00:01:06,355 --> 00:01:07,355
Alright, next one, next one!

15
00:01:07,380 --> 00:01:08,421
Excuse me, excuse me, Ma’am.

16
00:01:08,572 --> 00:01:10,572
She even has a mic!
She’s holding a mic!

17
00:01:10,729 --> 00:01:15,243
Lola Maxi, which body part
would you want to change, if any?

18
00:01:15,754 --> 00:01:19,980
Actually, none, because
I love my long-legged.

19
00:01:20,050 --> 00:01:21,564
Applause, applause!

20
00:01:21,589 --> 00:01:24,652
Alright, hand me the mic!
Give me it to me.

21
00:01:24,858 --> 00:01:25,858
Thank you, excuse me.

22
00:01:26,131 --> 00:01:28,524
Contestant number three,
how are you?!

23
00:01:29,192 --> 00:01:31,825
I’m fine! Fine like a fine tree.

24
00:01:31,850 --> 00:01:35,506
Oh! She’s funny, she’s funny!
Question, question, question.

25
00:01:35,988 --> 00:01:38,481
How many islands are
there in the Philippines?

26
00:01:38,978 --> 00:01:41,871
Uh, high tide or low tide?

27
00:01:41,896 --> 00:01:44,292
Alright, applause!

28
00:01:44,574 --> 00:01:47,585
I think I’ve seen her
before! I have a crush on her!

29
00:01:47,610 --> 00:01:50,113
Speaking of, I remember something.

30
00:01:50,683 --> 00:01:53,390
That time we held a
beauty pageant, right?

31
00:01:53,647 --> 00:01:54,647
- Yeah!
- Right?!

32
00:01:54,652 --> 00:01:57,949
I loved the winner!
And the first runner-up too!

33
00:01:58,003 --> 00:01:59,777
What even happened back then?

34
00:01:59,808 --> 00:02:01,381
Well, Lola Maxi,

35
00:02:01,695 --> 00:02:04,382
it started when Tash and I thought of…

36
00:02:05,741 --> 00:02:09,234
- Queen-Saymada 2024!
- Queen-Saymada 2024!

37
00:03:11,939 --> 00:03:13,268
Take some. Dad,

38
00:03:13,293 --> 00:03:19,596
um, Kuya Andres and I were thinking
of holding an event to promote the bakery.

39
00:03:19,990 --> 00:03:22,224
Here in Barangay Singko.

40
00:03:22,854 --> 00:03:26,871
Dad, just a competition,
to bring in a lot of people here.

41
00:03:27,637 --> 00:03:32,297
Mmm, that sounds exhausting,
Tash, and Andres!

42
00:03:32,322 --> 00:03:36,495
Yeah! And we’re busy with so much already!
What’s your plan for this?!

43
00:03:36,921 --> 00:03:38,635
- Kuya Iskineport, Kuya Chard…
- Mm?

44
00:03:39,052 --> 00:03:40,132
It’s a beauty pageant!

45
00:03:40,157 --> 00:03:42,167
A beauty pageant?!
Oh, I have time for that!

46
00:03:42,223 --> 00:03:45,130
We can make time for anything!

47
00:03:45,192 --> 00:03:46,199
So, when’s this happening?

48
00:03:46,245 --> 00:03:49,291
It’s a gay beauty pageant
because it’s more fun, right?!

49
00:03:49,316 --> 00:03:52,395
Oh, someone just texted me.
I have plans that day.

50
00:03:52,772 --> 00:03:54,325
I’m on board for that, bro.

51
00:03:55,272 --> 00:03:59,303
They’re right, but you know,
Andres, Atasha,

52
00:03:59,407 --> 00:04:02,100
the expenses, the workload—

53
00:04:02,307 --> 00:04:03,880
what if it all just goes to waste?

54
00:04:03,905 --> 00:04:07,348
Well, good thing
we’ve planned everything!

55
00:04:07,410 --> 00:04:09,976
Here’s the cost estimate.

56
00:04:10,527 --> 00:04:12,680
And here’s the project.

57
00:04:12,772 --> 00:04:13,928
- Project Ensaymada?
- So…

58
00:04:13,953 --> 00:04:16,046
- you got this?
- Yes!

59
00:04:16,089 --> 00:04:18,149
Sponsored by Bake Haus of U!

60
00:04:18,738 --> 00:04:20,151
- You can do this?
- For sure!

61
00:04:20,250 --> 00:04:24,947
And Dad, Mom,
here’s the budget calculation.

62
00:04:25,041 --> 00:04:26,041
Okay?

63
00:04:26,066 --> 00:04:29,160
The costs are low,
and the expected return is high.

64
00:04:29,270 --> 00:04:30,790
Wait, wait, my love, look at this!

65
00:04:31,290 --> 00:04:33,416
I think we can do it!

66
00:04:33,765 --> 00:04:36,258
What do you think? Let’s try it out.

67
00:04:38,284 --> 00:04:39,284
Hmmm.

68
00:04:39,348 --> 00:04:40,348
It’s up to you!

69
00:04:40,559 --> 00:04:42,069
Alright, okay!

70
00:04:42,343 --> 00:04:43,645
- Really?! Really?!
- Okay!

71
00:04:51,911 --> 00:04:53,278
Anne, close the shop!

72
00:04:53,531 --> 00:04:54,784
- Why?
- We need to close up,

73
00:04:54,809 --> 00:04:56,066
there are spies lurking!

74
00:04:56,867 --> 00:04:59,847
BFF! Come on,
I’m not here to spy.

75
00:05:02,723 --> 00:05:09,593
I just wanted to ask if I could
hang a poster in your bakery?

76
00:05:09,618 --> 00:05:11,321
We’re promoting an event.

77
00:05:11,906 --> 00:05:18,320
Queen-Saymada 2024!
You’re fabulous, Tito Aga!

78
00:05:18,345 --> 00:05:19,739
You think so?
BFF,

79
00:05:21,093 --> 00:05:24,846
I know our bakeries are competitors,

80
00:05:24,928 --> 00:05:29,156
but you know,
our friendship means more to me.

81
00:05:29,240 --> 00:05:30,240
Hmm.

82
00:05:30,458 --> 00:05:31,458
So...

83
00:05:31,648 --> 00:05:32,855
The audacity of this guy.

84
00:05:33,068 --> 00:05:34,068
What did you say?

85
00:05:34,574 --> 00:05:35,574
Nothing!

86
00:05:36,415 --> 00:05:38,002
Dragging me into this...

87
00:05:42,008 --> 00:05:44,049
but if this project of his
becomes successful,

88
00:05:44,666 --> 00:05:46,175
I’ll be left behind!

89
00:05:46,502 --> 00:05:48,114
That can’t happen,
him being the only star?

90
00:05:48,581 --> 00:05:49,581
No way!

91
00:05:50,801 --> 00:05:51,801
- BFF?
- BFF!

92
00:05:51,804 --> 00:05:54,024
You seem like
you’re talking to yourself.

93
00:05:54,049 --> 00:05:56,495
Of course, I’ll support you!

94
00:05:56,520 --> 00:05:57,520
Really?!

95
00:05:57,545 --> 00:05:59,352
Yes! We’ll co-sponsor!

96
00:06:00,723 --> 00:06:01,723
Co-sponsor?

97
00:06:01,748 --> 00:06:04,575
Whatever you put in,
I’ll match it!

98
00:06:04,991 --> 00:06:10,283
50-50, but you have to promote
my bakery too. Fair’s fair!

99
00:06:10,308 --> 00:06:12,928
Oh, the kids will be
thrilled when I tell them!

100
00:06:12,953 --> 00:06:13,953
Who are you telling?

101
00:06:13,978 --> 00:06:14,978
My kids!

102
00:06:15,003 --> 00:06:18,153
Oh, don’t just tell the kids.
Tell the adults too.

103
00:06:20,156 --> 00:06:21,310
I’m excited!

104
00:06:22,853 --> 00:06:24,933
- Thank you, thank you, thank you so much!
- You’re welcome!

105
00:06:24,958 --> 00:06:26,508
No, but really. Thank
you, thank you so much.

106
00:06:26,606 --> 00:06:31,358
Stop being so touchy with me.
It’s giving me goosebumps!

107
00:06:31,383 --> 00:06:32,383
No, it’s not!

108
00:06:32,405 --> 00:06:35,012
It’s embarrassing.
Imagine people passing by,

109
00:06:35,036 --> 00:06:37,437
seeing us like this.
They’ll think we’re... you know!

110
00:06:37,508 --> 00:06:40,675
No one’s going to think that!
I’m married with kids!

111
00:06:40,902 --> 00:06:42,595
I’m so excited, BFF!

112
00:06:44,836 --> 00:06:46,823
That’s what bothers me—you’re so intense!

113
00:06:47,371 --> 00:06:48,371
Why?!

114
00:06:49,466 --> 00:06:50,466
Why?!

115
00:06:50,918 --> 00:06:54,182
I’m frustrated with you!

116
00:06:54,422 --> 00:06:57,715
Miss Queen-Saymada 2024?!

117
00:06:58,126 --> 00:06:59,999
- I love it!
- Really?!

118
00:07:00,024 --> 00:07:02,529
Do you have a host already?
Because I want to volunteer as host!

119
00:07:02,742 --> 00:07:05,217
- Yes!
- Of course, you’re always welcome.

120
00:07:05,242 --> 00:07:09,773
Tito Iskineport is hosting too,
but it’d be great if it’s both of you!

121
00:07:10,013 --> 00:07:12,977
Oh, I’d rather not,
but fine, fine. Whatever.

122
00:07:13,002 --> 00:07:15,863
Boss Beauty, maybe you’d like
to join the pageant?

123
00:07:15,989 --> 00:07:19,095
In case you didn’t know,
I used to be a pageant queen.

124
00:07:19,963 --> 00:07:21,856
And I’m great at Q&A.

125
00:07:22,180 --> 00:07:24,814
I always win!

126
00:07:25,926 --> 00:07:28,273
Oh, great!
You’re perfect for this competition!

127
00:07:32,289 --> 00:07:34,109
Always winning?!

128
00:07:36,796 --> 00:07:39,450
Don’t make me laugh… Badong!

129
00:07:40,455 --> 00:07:45,010
So embarrassing.
Anxiety M. Pedro!

130
00:07:45,670 --> 00:07:46,670
You’re right.

131
00:07:46,907 --> 00:07:48,381
I’m your anxiety!

132
00:07:48,954 --> 00:07:53,087
Call me Pretty, Boss Pretty!

133
00:07:53,256 --> 00:07:54,256
Pretty?

134
00:07:54,281 --> 00:08:02,473
You may win, but only as first runner-up
because I’m always the winner!

135
00:08:02,906 --> 00:08:03,973
Hey, you!

136
00:08:04,432 --> 00:08:05,712
Get out of here!

137
00:08:06,434 --> 00:08:07,594
I was on my way out anyway.

138
00:08:08,262 --> 00:08:11,188
I just heard about the pageant here.

139
00:08:12,008 --> 00:08:13,008
Is it true?

140
00:08:13,261 --> 00:08:14,354
Here’s a flyer for you.

141
00:08:14,632 --> 00:08:16,118
- Queen-Saymada!
- Thank you, baby boy!

142
00:08:17,326 --> 00:08:18,759
See you on stage!

143
00:08:19,921 --> 00:08:21,241
- Bye!
- Bye-bye!

144
00:08:21,553 --> 00:08:25,320
You look like NFA rice—so rough!

145
00:08:26,724 --> 00:08:28,430
That pest is trying to scare me!

146
00:08:28,852 --> 00:08:30,665
Like he’ll succeed!

147
00:08:33,124 --> 00:08:34,304
That was intense, huh?

148
00:08:34,948 --> 00:08:36,494
- Who was that?
- Yeah, who was that?

149
00:08:37,081 --> 00:08:38,081
Yeah.

150
00:08:38,573 --> 00:08:39,573
Oh,

151
00:08:40,553 --> 00:08:42,077
that’s my ex…

152
00:08:42,501 --> 00:08:43,669
- Ex?!
- Ex?!

153
00:08:43,694 --> 00:08:45,435
- Ex?!
- Ex… best friend.

154
00:08:47,376 --> 00:08:48,550
And she better be ready.

155
00:08:50,505 --> 00:08:51,505
Wow!

156
00:08:51,541 --> 00:08:54,448
Boss Beauty and her best friend
actually joined, huh?

157
00:08:54,479 --> 00:08:55,485
Ex-best friend!

158
00:08:55,750 --> 00:08:57,771
- Uh, ex.
- But yeah! It’s so exciting, right?

159
00:08:57,902 --> 00:08:58,636
- But yeah! It’s so exciting, right?
- Right?!

160
00:08:58,661 --> 00:09:02,422
Yes, but it’ll only be exciting if
they actually have an event to join,

161
00:09:02,502 --> 00:09:05,568
and there’s still so much we
need to do on my checklist!

162
00:09:06,063 --> 00:09:08,003
Maybe we can move the event?

163
00:09:08,258 --> 00:09:09,438
Are you serious, Kuya?

164
00:09:09,869 --> 00:09:11,042
We can’t do that!

165
00:09:11,415 --> 00:09:15,895
Mom and Dad only allowed us to do
this so we could prove we can manage.

166
00:09:16,044 --> 00:09:19,377
If we move the event,
the whole thing would be wasted—

167
00:09:19,402 --> 00:09:22,867
Tash, calm down!
You’re stressing out again! What is it?

168
00:09:22,892 --> 00:09:24,816
- Because look—
- Hey, you two!

169
00:09:25,059 --> 00:09:29,212
I’m here as a representative for Tso K,
not a referee, okay?

170
00:09:30,225 --> 00:09:33,140
So, what should we do?
What’s missing?

171
00:09:33,165 --> 00:09:38,396
I need program spiels, a script,
set decorations, and a performer!

172
00:09:38,809 --> 00:09:41,622
Okay, fine. I’ll handle the flow, and—

173
00:09:41,668 --> 00:09:43,595
- I’ll take care of the decor.
- Alright.

174
00:09:43,620 --> 00:09:44,847
- So, I guess I’ll handle the performer?
- Yeah!

175
00:09:44,872 --> 00:09:46,761
Alright! Let’s do this!

176
00:09:48,118 --> 00:09:49,118
Okay, got it.

177
00:09:54,512 --> 00:09:55,512
Psst!

178
00:09:55,826 --> 00:09:56,826
Hey, handsome!

179
00:09:57,985 --> 00:09:58,985
Hey!

180
00:10:00,399 --> 00:10:01,399
Can I buy you?

181
00:10:01,504 --> 00:10:02,637
Wow, this guy!

182
00:10:02,691 --> 00:10:04,171
I’m not for sale, you know!

183
00:10:04,301 --> 00:10:05,389
No, not that.

184
00:10:05,413 --> 00:10:09,308
I mean, can I buy a high score
at Queen-Saymada 2024?

185
00:10:09,333 --> 00:10:10,333
You’re a judge, right?

186
00:10:10,745 --> 00:10:13,866
Yeah, so why would I help you?

187
00:10:14,221 --> 00:10:15,827
I’ve done my research,

188
00:10:16,382 --> 00:10:20,122
and I heard you were betrayed!

189
00:10:22,112 --> 00:10:24,799
So sad, makes me wanna cry.

190
00:10:25,177 --> 00:10:27,598
But honestly, I can relate.

191
00:10:29,008 --> 00:10:30,008
How so?

192
00:10:31,458 --> 00:10:32,458
Cue music!

193
00:10:48,371 --> 00:10:50,044
I once had a lover,

194
00:10:52,698 --> 00:10:53,698
Badong.

195
00:10:53,723 --> 00:10:54,963
His name was Dudung.

196
00:10:56,104 --> 00:10:59,070
I thought he was the one for me,

197
00:11:01,007 --> 00:11:04,387
so I introduced him to everyone.

198
00:11:05,664 --> 00:11:06,737
But one day,

199
00:11:10,802 --> 00:11:14,295
I found out he was with someone else.

200
00:11:16,010 --> 00:11:17,010
Wow, that’s intense!

201
00:11:17,034 --> 00:11:19,380
Tso K, they’re really
good at twisting stories!

202
00:11:20,164 --> 00:11:22,204
- Oh…
- Speaking of twisting,

203
00:11:22,505 --> 00:11:24,478
do you know who
twisted things for me?

204
00:11:25,242 --> 00:11:28,008
It was none other than
my best friend, Badong.

205
00:11:29,203 --> 00:11:31,983
You know him as Boss Beauty.

206
00:11:32,653 --> 00:11:36,200
But I know him as a traitor!

207
00:11:38,474 --> 00:11:39,821
Do you know what it feels like

208
00:11:41,395 --> 00:11:42,849
when the person you love

209
00:11:44,851 --> 00:11:48,018
is taken by someone you trust?

210
00:11:51,673 --> 00:11:52,673
It hurts.

211
00:11:53,403 --> 00:11:56,555
It really, really hurts!

212
00:11:57,199 --> 00:12:02,867
So, I’m going to steal his dream
because he stole mine!

213
00:12:03,107 --> 00:12:04,107
Tso Ke –

214
00:12:04,282 --> 00:12:06,590
Stop saying Tso Ke!
It’s not Tso Ke!

215
00:12:06,804 --> 00:12:08,372
Tso K! Sorry, Tso K.

216
00:12:08,397 --> 00:12:10,640
You better be careful about
what you’re saying, alright?

217
00:12:10,671 --> 00:12:12,754
My apologies.
Um, so how much are you?

218
00:12:14,647 --> 00:12:16,654
I told you, I’m not for sale!

219
00:12:17,720 --> 00:12:19,500
But I’ll do this for free.

220
00:12:20,652 --> 00:12:22,012
I actually feel bad for you.

221
00:12:22,085 --> 00:12:23,085
Really?!

222
00:12:23,110 --> 00:12:24,956
But you’re right. I agree with you!

223
00:12:25,200 --> 00:12:27,113
Those who betray deserve to suffer!

224
00:12:27,500 --> 00:12:28,500
Exactly!

225
00:12:34,755 --> 00:12:36,742
Exactly!

226
00:12:39,253 --> 00:12:41,747
So that’s why you and Boss Pretty
don’t get along, huh?

227
00:12:42,997 --> 00:12:44,157
I’ve regretted it, honestly.

228
00:12:44,654 --> 00:12:46,214
Because in the end,
we didn’t even end up together.

229
00:12:46,742 --> 00:12:49,655
I apologized to Pedro, though.
But it was too late.

230
00:12:50,110 --> 00:12:54,490
You know, Boss Beauty, I’m not going
to condone what you did, but the thing is,

231
00:12:55,619 --> 00:13:00,320
he shouldn’t have directed
all his anger at you.

232
00:13:00,868 --> 00:13:01,894
That’s where he was wrong!

233
00:13:03,377 --> 00:13:08,914
What if I just let him win
so he can be happy?

234
00:13:09,654 --> 00:13:10,907
No, that’s wrong too.

235
00:13:10,932 --> 00:13:12,700
But what can I do?
He’s the one in the wrong, after all.

236
00:13:12,861 --> 00:13:15,871
Don’t worry, Boss Beauty!

237
00:13:16,097 --> 00:13:20,690
Did you know
I was once a beauty queen?

238
00:13:20,715 --> 00:13:21,715
No way!

239
00:13:22,070 --> 00:13:24,116
- Really, Ate Cha?! That’s surprising!
- Yes!

240
00:13:24,404 --> 00:13:27,824
I was Miss Universe... ity.

241
00:13:28,428 --> 00:13:30,741
I represented our college!

242
00:13:31,270 --> 00:13:32,703
Can’t you tell?

243
00:13:33,019 --> 00:13:38,996
Wow, Ate Cha! If you teach me and
I win, I’ll give you two sacks of rice!

244
00:13:39,247 --> 00:13:40,853
One already cooked!

245
00:13:41,395 --> 00:13:42,702
I’ll cook it myself!

246
00:13:43,598 --> 00:13:49,168
Wait a minute!
Can I get an advance on one sack?

247
00:13:49,297 --> 00:13:51,464
- Right now?
- Oh, my love!

248
00:13:51,786 --> 00:13:53,606
- What?!
- We can’t do that!

249
00:13:53,631 --> 00:13:56,022
- What’s wrong with you?!
- But she said—

250
00:13:56,152 --> 00:13:57,739
We’re the organizers, aren’t we?!

251
00:13:57,983 --> 00:14:03,309
Of course, if the other contestants
find out we’re biased, they’ll be hurt.

252
00:14:03,731 --> 00:14:09,644
Besides, there’s nothing wrong
with giving you tips, right?

253
00:14:10,022 --> 00:14:12,369
I’ll teach you how to do the pasarela!

254
00:14:12,394 --> 00:14:14,181
- I love that, I love that! Pasarela!
- Pasarela?

255
00:14:14,241 --> 00:14:15,514
Should we start now?

256
00:14:15,539 --> 00:14:17,905
- Let’s go, let’s go!
- Come on, let’s start here!

257
00:14:18,149 --> 00:14:20,249
My love, my love!
Are you serious about what you’re doing?

258
00:14:20,274 --> 00:14:21,958
Yes, I am! Just listen to me!

259
00:14:21,983 --> 00:14:22,983
- I’ve never seen this before!
- Okay!

260
00:14:23,007 --> 00:14:27,000
Shoulders back!
Stand tall, long neck!

261
00:14:27,160 --> 00:14:30,373
And pretend there’s a
string pulling you upward!

262
00:14:30,558 --> 00:14:34,269
Okay! And when we walk,
sway your hips, alright?

263
00:14:34,374 --> 00:14:35,420
Right, left.

264
00:14:35,460 --> 00:14:36,720
Alright, let’s start. Here we go!

265
00:14:37,541 --> 00:14:41,011
Sway, sway, sway, sway, sway!

266
00:14:41,036 --> 00:14:42,689
At the end, let’s do a turn, okay?

267
00:14:42,714 --> 00:14:45,511
One, two, three, turn! Bam!

268
00:14:46,458 --> 00:14:49,597
And we’re back
with the competition

269
00:14:49,621 --> 00:14:51,810
that’s hotter than fresh
bread out of the oven!

270
00:14:52,009 --> 00:14:56,009
This is Queen-Saymada 2024!

271
00:14:58,390 --> 00:15:02,650
Now, let’s call on
candidate number three!

272
00:15:06,008 --> 00:15:08,161
I’m Umami Tsunami,

273
00:15:08,454 --> 00:15:10,181
and I’m here to say,

274
00:15:10,839 --> 00:15:18,427
“Why would you need bread
if not to stuff your dad’s brasserie?”

275
00:15:21,816 --> 00:15:22,856
Amazing!

276
00:15:23,152 --> 00:15:27,075
Now, let’s call on
candidate number four!

277
00:15:28,279 --> 00:15:29,426
Boss Beauty!

278
00:15:29,559 --> 00:15:30,839
Boss Beauty!

279
00:15:31,119 --> 00:15:32,212
Boss Beauty!

280
00:15:32,496 --> 00:15:33,763
Boss Beauty!

281
00:15:35,368 --> 00:15:39,441
From the land of the sun,
sea, and moon—

282
00:15:39,716 --> 00:15:40,976
San Simun!

283
00:15:44,074 --> 00:15:46,728
My name is Boss Beauty,

284
00:15:46,982 --> 00:15:49,896
but tonight,
let me introduce myself

285
00:15:50,173 --> 00:15:56,500
as the woman who once broke the
picky heart of Mr. Roderick Paulate.

286
00:15:57,450 --> 00:16:02,958
Yes, that’s right,
I am Miss Jackie Aquino!

287
00:16:12,075 --> 00:16:13,395
Boss Beauty!

288
00:16:13,886 --> 00:16:14,959
Boss Beauty!

289
00:16:14,984 --> 00:16:19,176
Now, let’s call on
candidate number five!

290
00:16:20,653 --> 00:16:21,846
Whooo!

291
00:16:24,729 --> 00:16:29,656
By the way,
my name is Preeeeeeetty!

292
00:16:29,973 --> 00:16:31,293
I have a coat.

293
00:16:41,738 --> 00:16:44,382
A beautiful coat. Thank you!

294
00:16:46,130 --> 00:16:48,460
- Yay!
- I’m so nervous!

295
00:16:48,485 --> 00:16:52,109
Our candidates are amazing,
right, Iskineport?

296
00:16:52,134 --> 00:16:53,134
Mmm…

297
00:16:53,643 --> 00:16:57,476
Alright, good evening,
Barangay Singko!

298
00:16:58,240 --> 00:17:01,923
Who will be the Queen
who’s got the most to say in the Q&A

299
00:17:01,948 --> 00:17:06,839
and can serve talent like boom,
yes, girl, ey, get it!

300
00:17:06,864 --> 00:17:13,170
This is Queen-Saymada 2024!

301
00:17:14,884 --> 00:17:15,884
Your turn!

302
00:17:18,520 --> 00:17:20,387
Our… alright, I’ll do it.

303
00:17:20,412 --> 00:17:26,392
Our titleholder
will take home ₱10,000

304
00:17:27,095 --> 00:17:34,211
and, of course, a year’s supply of
ensaymada from our official sponsors—

305
00:17:34,306 --> 00:17:39,519
Bake Haus of U and Bake K Naman!

306
00:17:39,920 --> 00:17:44,693
Iskineport, do you want to
introduce our board of judges?

307
00:17:46,088 --> 00:17:47,088
You do it…

308
00:17:47,268 --> 00:17:48,614
Compose yourself.

309
00:17:48,687 --> 00:17:52,320
Alright, alright.
At this point, let’s introduce them.

310
00:17:52,445 --> 00:18:02,419
First on the list, the oldest baker in
Barangay Singko—let’s call on Lola Maxi!

311
00:18:05,643 --> 00:18:08,302
Lola Maxi, you’re a legend, we love you!

312
00:18:08,327 --> 00:18:11,710
We’re so lucky she’s still alive!

313
00:18:14,540 --> 00:18:15,940
Lola Maxi, relax!

314
00:18:16,159 --> 00:18:17,986
Okay, Lola Maxi!

315
00:18:19,578 --> 00:18:22,098
All I can say is… everyone’s great!

316
00:18:22,790 --> 00:18:24,464
Pop off, sis!

317
00:18:24,774 --> 00:18:28,701
Boogsh! On point!
Slay, girl! Rawr!

318
00:18:30,022 --> 00:18:31,042
Gen Z!

319
00:18:31,968 --> 00:18:32,975
- Gen Z!
- I love it!

320
00:18:33,050 --> 00:18:34,163
Gen Z!

321
00:18:34,542 --> 00:18:35,542
Yes!

322
00:18:35,700 --> 00:18:39,433
Iskineport, do you want to
introduce our next judge?

323
00:18:39,471 --> 00:18:42,038
You do it, or I might not
make it to season two!

324
00:18:43,334 --> 00:18:45,587
Alright, fine, I’ll do it
to keep you safe.

325
00:18:46,037 --> 00:18:52,975
Our next judge is the dashing
owner of Bake Haus of U,

326
00:18:53,000 --> 00:19:00,317
who’s always staring at
Ate Cha—Mr. Aga Pers!

327
00:19:00,580 --> 00:19:03,772
I got nervous there.
Thank you, thank you!

328
00:19:04,253 --> 00:19:07,246
Anyway, may the best queen win!

329
00:19:10,292 --> 00:19:17,935
And of course, our final judge,
the super fresh, daddy-type

330
00:19:18,503 --> 00:19:24,286
owner of Bake K Naman, Tso K!

331
00:19:24,446 --> 00:19:25,446
Tso K!

332
00:19:25,492 --> 00:19:26,492
Tso K!

333
00:19:26,638 --> 00:19:27,692
All I have to say is…

334
00:19:28,962 --> 00:19:30,222
they’re all ugly!

335
00:19:30,666 --> 00:19:31,666
Whoo!

336
00:19:31,723 --> 00:19:35,390
Except for candidate number five!

337
00:19:50,158 --> 00:19:51,825
You’re not…
You’re not going to win like this!

338
00:19:52,604 --> 00:19:54,014
Hand me that water; I’m thirsty!

339
00:19:54,039 --> 00:19:56,223
- What’s wrong with you? That’s mine!
- Just a sip!

340
00:19:56,248 --> 00:19:57,630
- You’re always like this, stealing things!
- Just a sip!

341
00:19:57,942 --> 00:19:59,522
Now the seahorse is wet!

342
00:20:00,146 --> 00:20:02,832
Andres, why didn’t you rent a tent?!

343
00:20:02,857 --> 00:20:03,857
How was I supposed to know?

344
00:20:04,265 --> 00:20:06,138
You told me to focus
on the stage, didn’t you?

345
00:20:06,367 --> 00:20:08,300
You said that!
You specifically said that!

346
00:20:08,344 --> 00:20:10,890
A tent! Now they’re all
changing clothes in our house!

347
00:20:11,376 --> 00:20:13,183
Well, you didn’t make it clear, Tash!

348
00:20:13,260 --> 00:20:15,673
And where are the sash
and the crown?!

349
00:20:15,884 --> 00:20:17,184
Will they make it
in time for the awarding?

350
00:20:18,173 --> 00:20:19,173
Hello?

351
00:20:19,198 --> 00:20:21,171
Uh, would you like to
upsize your order?

352
00:20:21,332 --> 00:20:22,332
Huh?

353
00:20:22,833 --> 00:20:24,593
- What for?
- You ordered too much!

354
00:20:25,141 --> 00:20:26,647
Can we void it, Ma’am?
Can we void it?

355
00:20:26,672 --> 00:20:30,426
You said, ‘I got this!’ You—

356
00:20:32,941 --> 00:20:33,941
Stop it, both of you!

357
00:20:34,432 --> 00:20:36,704
Tash, is the singer ready?

358
00:20:37,538 --> 00:20:38,538
Singer?

359
00:20:39,228 --> 00:20:40,228
Singer?!

360
00:20:43,327 --> 00:20:44,340
Nice, nice, nice!

361
00:21:02,901 --> 00:21:04,528
Nice! Nice!

362
00:21:04,741 --> 00:21:05,741
Great!

363
00:21:05,927 --> 00:21:07,274
Did you enjoy it?
Wasn’t it amazing?

364
00:21:08,525 --> 00:21:10,071
What happened there?
Why did you give it a five?

365
00:21:10,626 --> 00:21:11,713
Why are you interfering?

366
00:21:11,913 --> 00:21:13,226
- Yeah, exactly!
- This is my opinion!

367
00:21:13,250 --> 00:21:14,765
That’s what I wanted
to give her!

368
00:21:14,796 --> 00:21:17,647
But Lola Maxi, I just want to say
the performance was excellent!

369
00:21:17,742 --> 00:21:19,154
- Yes, it was excellent.
- Did you see the—

370
00:21:19,179 --> 00:21:22,169
Don’t tell me what to do!
Focus on the performer!

371
00:21:22,194 --> 00:21:23,247
- Don’t interfere!
- Fair enough.

372
00:21:23,272 --> 00:21:24,923
- Alright!
- Next up,

373
00:21:24,948 --> 00:21:29,112
from Barangay Singko herself,

374
00:21:29,408 --> 00:21:33,856
let’s give a round of
applause for Boss Beauty!

375
00:21:34,796 --> 00:21:35,948
Boss Beauty!

376
00:21:36,293 --> 00:21:37,712
Boss Beauty!

377
00:21:38,104 --> 00:21:39,613
Boss Beauty!

378
00:21:39,934 --> 00:21:40,934
Whoa!

379
00:22:09,946 --> 00:22:12,153
Pedro! What are you doing?!

380
00:22:12,866 --> 00:22:14,508
This is my masterpiece too!

381
00:22:15,082 --> 00:22:20,339
I joined in so everyone could see who’s
more fabulous between the two of us!

382
00:22:20,893 --> 00:22:21,893
Oh, really?!

383
00:22:31,765 --> 00:22:32,771
Hey, hey!

384
00:22:34,580 --> 00:22:35,859
You’re really going too far!

385
00:22:49,382 --> 00:22:53,875
For Beauty—five!
Beauty gets a five!

386
00:22:54,286 --> 00:22:55,626
Ten, ten!

387
00:22:55,651 --> 00:22:57,190
Their performance was good too!

388
00:22:57,766 --> 00:22:59,008
Pretty gets a ten!

389
00:22:59,113 --> 00:23:00,446
Here, now I’m in my element!

390
00:23:00,471 --> 00:23:05,483
And we're back here in
Queen-Saymada 2024!

391
00:23:05,508 --> 00:23:08,051
Ah, neighbors, hello!

392
00:23:08,168 --> 00:23:11,423
Apologies for the commotion earlier.

393
00:23:11,823 --> 00:23:15,120
There was just a little misunderstanding.

394
00:23:15,242 --> 00:23:16,975
- Right, Iskineport?
- Yes.

395
00:23:18,242 --> 00:23:19,242
Yes, I’m so nervous.

396
00:23:19,711 --> 00:23:21,901
Nothing, he's back to normal now.

397
00:23:22,212 --> 00:23:23,212
You okay?

398
00:23:23,237 --> 00:23:25,273
Anyway, moving on—

399
00:23:25,298 --> 00:23:28,393
don’t make noise if you
don’t have anything to say!—

400
00:23:28,787 --> 00:23:32,310
While our candidates
are changing outfits,

401
00:23:32,687 --> 00:23:39,788
we’ll have a very special performance
from Barangay Singko’s very own—

402
00:23:40,156 --> 00:23:41,156
Excuse me!

403
00:23:41,953 --> 00:23:43,692
Sorry, but, ah…

404
00:23:44,486 --> 00:23:46,335
we don’t have a performer today.

405
00:23:46,765 --> 00:23:47,820
- What?
- Why?

406
00:23:47,954 --> 00:23:50,505
Sorry, Mom. Sorry, Dad.

407
00:23:50,556 --> 00:23:54,293
We don’t have a performer,
but I hope you all enjoy—

408
00:23:54,318 --> 00:23:58,506
Let’s welcome Andres Pers!

409
00:23:59,161 --> 00:24:00,161
What?!

410
00:24:01,280 --> 00:24:02,280
Yes!

411
00:24:12,848 --> 00:24:14,605
Good evening, Barangay Singko!

412
00:24:15,359 --> 00:24:18,110
I won’t sing,
but I’ll perform some magic!

413
00:24:21,978 --> 00:24:23,687
For my first trick—what color is this?!

414
00:24:24,160 --> 00:24:25,445
- Black!
- White!

415
00:24:25,470 --> 00:24:26,666
- Black!
- Yellow!

416
00:24:27,779 --> 00:24:28,779
Silver!

417
00:24:29,142 --> 00:24:30,851
Yellow!

418
00:24:32,411 --> 00:24:34,496
What color is this?!
What color is this?!

419
00:24:35,515 --> 00:24:36,109
What color is this?!

420
00:24:36,246 --> 00:24:37,501
- Yellow!
- Blue!

421
00:24:38,197 --> 00:24:40,490
Black!

422
00:24:46,657 --> 00:24:47,657
Wow!

423
00:24:48,256 --> 00:24:49,559
Judge, how are you?

424
00:24:49,795 --> 00:24:51,316
Ah, I’m good, Sir!

425
00:24:51,588 --> 00:24:52,588
This is for you!

426
00:24:52,613 --> 00:24:54,242
- Hey, thanks!
- This is for you.

427
00:24:54,678 --> 00:24:56,086
- Hey!
- Hey, where’s mine?!

428
00:24:56,111 --> 00:24:57,188
- What?
- How many are there?

429
00:24:57,585 --> 00:24:59,653
Ah, one, two, three,
four, five, six, seven!

430
00:24:59,678 --> 00:25:01,420
- Six… seven.
- You can count. Do it.

431
00:25:01,497 --> 00:25:02,752
- Just put them in.
- Okay?

432
00:25:03,574 --> 00:25:04,817
Hurry up, just put them in!

433
00:25:05,419 --> 00:25:06,886
- Yes, please!
- Oh, there’s one more!

434
00:25:07,443 --> 00:25:09,074
- I’m getting butterflies!
- Oh!

435
00:25:12,509 --> 00:25:13,697
This magic is amazing!

436
00:25:18,463 --> 00:25:19,779
Amazing!

437
00:25:21,742 --> 00:25:23,373
For my last trick!

438
00:25:25,234 --> 00:25:26,973
I need a volunteer!

439
00:25:27,074 --> 00:25:28,074
Volunteer!

440
00:25:28,297 --> 00:25:29,412
- I volunteer!
- This one!

441
00:25:30,436 --> 00:25:31,436
Anne, come here.

442
00:25:31,849 --> 00:25:32,849
Hey, stand up!

443
00:25:35,866 --> 00:25:37,472
Please introduce yourself
to the crowd!

444
00:25:38,572 --> 00:25:40,766
Hello, my name is Anne.

445
00:25:40,791 --> 00:25:41,791
Yaaay!

446
00:25:43,551 --> 00:25:44,679
For my final trick,

447
00:25:47,150 --> 00:25:48,150
please blow!

448
00:25:57,309 --> 00:26:00,824
- Whoa!
- Okay, okay…

449
00:26:11,295 --> 00:26:16,507
One, two, three, magic!

450
00:26:25,989 --> 00:26:27,074
That was so good!

451
00:26:27,784 --> 00:26:28,784
That was so good!

452
00:26:29,725 --> 00:26:30,725
I really was, right?

453
00:26:48,524 --> 00:26:49,524
Wow!

454
00:26:54,363 --> 00:26:57,388
It’s like you brought
magic here, huh!

455
00:26:57,842 --> 00:26:58,933
Aw, don’t mention it.

456
00:26:58,958 --> 00:27:01,275
You were amazing, Orb, really!
I mean it.

457
00:27:01,572 --> 00:27:03,415
Thanks for joining me there, Anne.

458
00:27:04,596 --> 00:27:05,596
Of course!

459
00:27:09,567 --> 00:27:12,747
Andres, I’m sorry for the chaos.

460
00:27:13,289 --> 00:27:17,180
Despite that,
you covered for me.

461
00:27:18,006 --> 00:27:20,067
Thank you, sorry.

462
00:27:20,116 --> 00:27:23,019
Of course, we’re partners here, right?

463
00:27:23,377 --> 00:27:25,947
Sometimes, we misunderstand each other,

464
00:27:26,870 --> 00:27:28,410
but at the end of the day,

465
00:27:29,287 --> 00:27:30,942
we’ve got each other’s backs, right?

466
00:27:31,766 --> 00:27:32,766
- Right?
- Yeah!

467
00:27:33,241 --> 00:27:34,241
True!

468
00:27:46,922 --> 00:27:48,764
And I, thank you!

469
00:27:52,840 --> 00:27:55,646
Thank you! Good answer, right?!

470
00:27:57,573 --> 00:27:59,509
- I’m still nervous!
- Alright, that’s enough.

471
00:27:59,550 --> 00:28:07,471
Now, let’s call on Boss Pretty
to answer a question from Tso K!

472
00:28:12,097 --> 00:28:13,097
Alright!

473
00:28:14,046 --> 00:28:15,046
Here’s your question:

474
00:28:16,492 --> 00:28:19,358
What is your definition of “crush”?

475
00:28:24,311 --> 00:28:29,814
As a graduate of the Polytechnic University
of the Philippines, Major in Microbiology…

476
00:28:30,241 --> 00:28:31,283
What was the question again?

477
00:28:32,840 --> 00:28:33,840
Can you repeat it, Sir?

478
00:28:33,865 --> 00:28:35,892
What’s the question again?
What’s the question again?

479
00:28:36,611 --> 00:28:40,562
What is your definition of “crush”?

480
00:28:42,818 --> 00:28:46,911
Well, crush is admiration.

481
00:28:47,079 --> 00:28:48,413
- Thank you!
- That’s it! So good!

482
00:28:49,035 --> 00:28:50,108
So good!

483
00:28:50,356 --> 00:28:55,241
I cried at that, I was touched by that!
Stop, you were amazing!

484
00:28:55,434 --> 00:28:56,718
Winner material!

485
00:28:56,912 --> 00:28:57,912
Ten!

486
00:28:57,943 --> 00:28:58,943
Ten!

487
00:28:59,507 --> 00:29:00,877
Tso K, are you sure?

488
00:29:01,194 --> 00:29:03,521
Define “crush”?
Why does it feel so shallow?!

489
00:29:03,546 --> 00:29:07,208
No! The answer was deep!
Deep! I cried!

490
00:29:07,385 --> 00:29:10,019
What do you mean you cried? The question
was so simple, then you gave it a ten?

491
00:29:10,983 --> 00:29:12,135
That’s what I’m giving—a ten!

492
00:29:13,167 --> 00:29:14,834
Alright, if you say so.

493
00:29:16,689 --> 00:29:19,222
Now, last but not the least!

494
00:29:19,288 --> 00:29:23,445
To answer a question
from Mr. Aga Pers…

495
00:29:23,470 --> 00:29:27,735
- Oh, thank you!
- …let’s call on Boss Beauty!

496
00:29:31,020 --> 00:29:32,650
Good evening to you, Boss Beauty!

497
00:29:32,800 --> 00:29:34,231
Good evening, Kuya Aga!

498
00:29:34,271 --> 00:29:36,368
Here’s my question—

499
00:29:36,888 --> 00:29:39,494
what’s harder for you:

500
00:29:40,719 --> 00:29:44,367
to forgive or to ask for forgiveness?

501
00:29:45,947 --> 00:29:47,160
That’s hard.

502
00:29:47,185 --> 00:29:48,883
- That’s tough!
- So tough!

503
00:29:54,027 --> 00:29:55,639
I’ve asked for forgiveness before,

504
00:29:56,793 --> 00:29:58,048
and it was very difficult.

505
00:29:59,145 --> 00:30:01,170
It really damages
your self-confidence.

506
00:30:03,014 --> 00:30:05,251
But for me,

507
00:30:06,271 --> 00:30:07,653
it’s harder to forgive.

508
00:30:13,650 --> 00:30:18,448
Because my best friend, Pedro,

509
00:30:21,928 --> 00:30:25,879
lived in anger and couldn’t forgive me.

510
00:30:28,094 --> 00:30:29,670
But it’s not just Pedro—

511
00:30:30,996 --> 00:30:33,972
I also lived in anger.

512
00:30:34,303 --> 00:30:35,303
At myself.

513
00:30:36,714 --> 00:30:39,223
And to this day,
I still can’t forgive myself.

514
00:30:41,662 --> 00:30:43,450
If I’m struggling with that,

515
00:30:45,553 --> 00:30:46,760
how much harder
must it be for Pedro?

516
00:30:51,488 --> 00:30:54,427
So, bestie,

517
00:30:56,320 --> 00:30:57,320
I’m sorry.

518
00:30:59,242 --> 00:31:00,503
I’m so sorry, bestie!

519
00:31:01,244 --> 00:31:02,244
Sorry!

520
00:31:03,580 --> 00:31:04,580
Sorry...

521
00:31:05,318 --> 00:31:07,506
Bestie, that’s enough!

522
00:31:08,732 --> 00:31:11,635
Didn’t you hear what the younger
ones said backstage earlier?

523
00:31:12,106 --> 00:31:13,106
Sometimes,

524
00:31:13,434 --> 00:31:15,495
even if we don’t understand each other,

525
00:31:16,354 --> 00:31:17,354
in the end,

526
00:31:17,620 --> 00:31:19,856
we’re still partners, okay?

527
00:31:19,952 --> 00:31:22,613
- Mm-hmm! Bestie!
- Bestie!

528
00:31:39,038 --> 00:31:41,541
I’m sorry too, bestie!

529
00:31:42,628 --> 00:31:43,973
Sorry!

530
00:31:47,040 --> 00:31:48,040
Bravo!

531
00:31:51,104 --> 00:31:53,413
I miss you, bestie!

532
00:31:54,866 --> 00:31:56,138
- Kuya Aga!
- Hmm?

533
00:31:56,242 --> 00:31:58,908
Tso K, thank you so much
for organizing this event.

534
00:31:59,141 --> 00:32:01,420
Because of this,
my bestie and I made up.

535
00:32:01,766 --> 00:32:05,951
Right! Thanks a lot,
Tso Ke, and Kuya Aga too.

536
00:32:05,999 --> 00:32:07,465
- This one keeps saying Tso Ke!
- Thank you so much!

537
00:32:08,734 --> 00:32:10,128
It’s all good, isn’t it?

538
00:32:10,205 --> 00:32:11,787
Oh, bestie!

539
00:32:11,812 --> 00:32:12,812
What?

540
00:32:12,945 --> 00:32:14,769
Look, he really looks like Dudung!

541
00:32:14,794 --> 00:32:16,194
Your breath stinks, bestie!

542
00:32:16,506 --> 00:32:17,506
Who?

543
00:32:17,531 --> 00:32:18,531
That one, over there!

544
00:32:18,556 --> 00:32:20,198
- Ah, Chard?
- Doesn’t he look exactly like him?

545
00:32:21,938 --> 00:32:22,938
You’re right!

546
00:32:24,027 --> 00:32:25,221
He looked just like that before!

547
00:32:25,246 --> 00:32:26,466
His eyes popping out,

548
00:32:26,593 --> 00:32:28,460
lips sticking forward, big teeth,

549
00:32:28,850 --> 00:32:30,189
ears like side mirrors,

550
00:32:30,214 --> 00:32:31,852
and his nose like a puppy’s.

551
00:32:32,194 --> 00:32:34,175
Put it all together,
he looks like a chihuahua!

552
00:32:35,022 --> 00:32:36,590
- That’s him!
- He really does!

553
00:32:36,615 --> 00:32:37,926
Introduce me, bestie!

554
00:32:37,951 --> 00:32:40,500
Alright, bestie! Since we’ve made up,
I’ll set you up!

555
00:32:43,185 --> 00:32:45,052
Wait, wait, wait! Let me ask.

556
00:32:45,533 --> 00:32:48,103
Is this the Dudung lookalike
you’re talking about?

557
00:32:48,606 --> 00:32:50,964
Is this the face you two
fought about for a year?

558
00:32:50,989 --> 00:32:52,017
Exactly like this!

559
00:32:52,918 --> 00:32:55,118
- Hi, I’m pretty!
- Hey, hold on!

560
00:32:55,395 --> 00:32:56,395
Calm down!

561
00:32:58,282 --> 00:32:59,476
BFF, calm down!

562
00:32:59,501 --> 00:33:00,501
What’s with you?

563
00:33:00,812 --> 00:33:02,927
You’re tickling me; stop that!

564
00:33:03,539 --> 00:33:05,224
Oh, sorry, sorry!
Give me a kiss on the cheek!

565
00:33:08,374 --> 00:33:09,374
So bold!

566
00:33:09,621 --> 00:33:10,621
But delicious!

567
00:33:11,306 --> 00:33:12,851
Yummy!  Aww!

568
00:33:12,968 --> 00:33:15,874
Go on, you two talk
over there, quick!

569
00:33:15,909 --> 00:33:19,446
- Ouch! Ouch, babe! That hurts!
- Babe already?! Babe so soon?!

570
00:33:19,833 --> 00:33:21,027
It’s really something, huh?

571
00:33:22,558 --> 00:33:24,237
So funny, huh?

572
00:33:28,629 --> 00:33:29,629
Hmmm…

573
00:33:35,162 --> 00:33:36,162
BFF!

574
00:33:36,693 --> 00:33:37,693
What?

575
00:33:39,150 --> 00:33:40,308
I just realized,

576
00:33:41,110 --> 00:33:43,153
I haven’t even apologized
to you, have I?

577
00:33:43,953 --> 00:33:44,953
For what?

578
00:33:45,824 --> 00:33:48,133
For ending up with… Cha.

579
00:33:50,295 --> 00:33:51,295
Oh, that?

580
00:33:52,354 --> 00:33:53,354
Forget about it,

581
00:33:54,371 --> 00:33:55,371
It’s nothing.

582
00:33:55,825 --> 00:33:58,031
I’ve moved on from that.

583
00:33:59,137 --> 00:34:00,414
- It’s all good now.
- You know,

584
00:34:00,786 --> 00:34:03,129
you’ve always let me have my way.

585
00:34:03,303 --> 00:34:06,067
You even let me
end up with Charlene.

586
00:34:06,231 --> 00:34:09,485
She’s my wife now; we have kids.

587
00:34:09,978 --> 00:34:13,502
- It’s like you’re family to us already.
- So now I’m family, huh?

588
00:34:14,907 --> 00:34:15,907
Made me a sibling.

589
00:34:16,687 --> 00:34:17,687
So, thank you so much.

590
00:34:17,735 --> 00:34:19,090
It’s nothing, it’s nothing!

591
00:34:19,301 --> 00:34:22,065
Really, it’s okay!

592
00:34:24,174 --> 00:34:25,174
No, really.

593
00:34:27,347 --> 00:34:29,407
I can handle it! I’m tough!

594
00:34:29,616 --> 00:34:30,950
No, I’m sorry. I mean it.

595
00:34:30,975 --> 00:34:35,070
Even my kids, they think
of you like… I’m sorry.

596
00:34:35,778 --> 00:34:36,778
Really, I am.

597
00:34:37,689 --> 00:34:38,689
What is this?

598
00:34:39,853 --> 00:34:41,533
- Hey!
- Why are you so soft?

599
00:34:42,342 --> 00:34:43,732
- BFF!
- What?!

600
00:34:43,757 --> 00:34:46,284
Listen to me,
I’m already apologizing!

601
00:34:46,309 --> 00:34:48,735
You’re apologizing,
but you’re squishing my face in it!

602
00:34:48,760 --> 00:34:51,153
That’s not—
Oh, come on!

603
00:34:51,519 --> 00:34:52,628
Thank you, really.

604
00:34:52,653 --> 00:34:53,653
It’s all good now!

605
00:34:53,847 --> 00:34:55,164
- Thank you.
- I’m tough!

606
00:34:56,646 --> 00:34:58,924
I forgive you, remember that!

607
00:34:58,991 --> 00:34:59,991
For tonight!

608
00:35:00,337 --> 00:35:01,337
Why only tonight?!

609
00:35:01,664 --> 00:35:04,543
Okay, fine. That’s good enough for me,
even just for tonight.

610
00:35:04,835 --> 00:35:05,835
Approved!

611
00:35:06,465 --> 00:35:08,883
What is this?
I’m getting annoyed now!

612
00:35:09,146 --> 00:35:10,146
No, really!

613
00:35:10,171 --> 00:35:12,078
Stop it—I don’t even understand anymore!

614
00:35:12,103 --> 00:35:13,979
I’m getting goosebumps, see?

615
00:35:14,004 --> 00:35:16,892
Oh, so that’s what happened!

616
00:35:17,921 --> 00:35:22,958
Yes, and honestly, ‘La,
we can actually do it again!

617
00:35:23,000 --> 00:35:25,443
Oh, Dad! No way!

618
00:35:25,468 --> 00:35:26,756
- Why not?
- Just no!

619
00:35:26,842 --> 00:35:28,787
Wait, where’s Anne?

620
00:35:28,961 --> 00:35:30,555
- Anne?
- Anne’s here?

621
00:35:30,593 --> 00:35:32,806
Yes, she just…
she just changed outfits.

622
00:35:32,975 --> 00:35:34,327
- Where?
- She’s upstairs! Over there.

623
00:35:34,483 --> 00:35:35,483
Where?

624
00:35:35,786 --> 00:35:37,493
Tada!

625
00:35:37,887 --> 00:35:38,887
Hey!

626
00:35:39,736 --> 00:35:41,154
Oh, gosh, look at her!

627
00:35:41,942 --> 00:35:43,288
That’s right, flaunt it!

628
00:35:44,688 --> 00:35:46,664
- Oh! Oh!
- Wow!

629
00:35:55,488 --> 00:35:56,906
Wow!

630
00:35:57,306 --> 00:35:59,373
You’re going to bump into me.
Come here already!

631
00:36:00,856 --> 00:36:02,256
You’re so extra!

632
00:36:02,689 --> 00:36:04,737
Anne, you’re so beautiful.

633
00:36:05,125 --> 00:36:08,253
- Hey!
- Hey! Are you crushing on me?

634
00:36:08,326 --> 00:36:09,326
You’re crazy!

635
00:36:11,673 --> 00:36:13,171
What is this… I mean,

636
00:36:13,195 --> 00:36:15,728
what I’m trying to say is
you’re so fun… to tease.

637
00:36:17,983 --> 00:36:21,110
You look… you look like you’re
wrapped in powdered rice cake!

638
00:36:21,135 --> 00:36:22,891
Hey! Oh, really?!

639
00:36:22,916 --> 00:36:24,287
Yes, really!

640
00:36:24,510 --> 00:36:25,954
- Wait, wait! Hold on!
- Wait!

641
00:36:25,979 --> 00:36:30,356
I just want to say I’m happy
we pulled off this event, right?

642
00:36:30,699 --> 00:36:38,667
Through struggles and joy,
Pers is first, Pers is the hero!
